    "en": {
      "title": "BASL condemns attacks on journalists, & calls for action against police officers for attacks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Bar Association of Sri Lanka convening a special press conference on Sunday (10) afternoon has condemned the violence that broke out on Saturday (9) during the mass protest against the President, Prime Minister, and the Government.",
        "BASL President Saliya Pieris, PC told reporters that the Bar Association of Sri Lanka condemned the shooting at protestors on Saturday (9) morning, the attacks on News 1st journalists later in the day, and the torching of the Prime Minister\u2019s residence on Saturday (9) night. The Bar Association President pointed out that disciplinary action must be taken against all police officers who attacked journalists following an impartial, and immediate investigation.",
        "\u201cAll acts of violence are condemned the should be investigated,\u201d he told reporters adding that it is important to protect the rights of journalists to report on the news.",
        "The President of the Bar Association of Sri Lanka urged Sri Lankans who are occupying the President\u2019s House and the President\u2019s Office to refrain from causing any damage to the property, especially those items of historical importance.",
        "\u201cWe must all understand that all acts of violence by any party in any form will destabilize, worsen the country\u2019s economy, and will worsen the plight of the people,\u201d he said.",
        "For this reason all Sri Lankans must step back from violence and understand that violence does not benefit anyone.",
        "BASL condemns attacks on journalists, & calls for action against police officers for attacks",
        "What happens after the President resigns? BASL explains process to elect new President",
        "President & PM have no moral right to remain in power; Sirisena writes 10-point letter to build Sri Lanka"
      ],
